t that they are construed as bundles of tropes. Apart from metaphysician colleagues, the book is recommended for advanced students in analytic metaphysics.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aIndividuation (Philosophy) 0aSubstance (Philosophy) 0aTropes (Philosophy) 4aOntologie. 4aPhilosophie. 70(DE-601)1051599130(DE-588)4202257-5aSubstanz2gnd 70(DE-601)1060853440(DE-588)4075660-9aOntologie2gnd 70(DE-601)6138197560(DE-588)7681866-4aTropegPhilosophie2gnd 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook Package De Gruyter Ontos 2002-2012z978311033122608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook Paket De Gruyter Ontos 2002-2012z9783110331219oZDB-23-DON0 cprintz978311032048040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110320664423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110320664.jpg  a978-3-11-023848-8  DGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-033122-6  eBook Package De Gruyter Ontos 2002-2012  aDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DONb2012  aZDB-23-GPHc2000d2014